description:
Has the surrender of Protestantism set the stage for last day events? For unity with Rome, Protestants have cast aside key Bible doctrines. But at what cost? And what will the results be?

In a highly significant move, Lutherans were the first of the Protestants to sign “From Conflict to Communion” and are working toward full visible unity with the Roman Catholic Church. Because the prophecies that were understood by the Reformers have been rejected, there is now a vagueness about what is happening in the world and Christians seem unaware of the danger signs.

What essential Bible doctrines have been laid aside by Protestants for unity with Rome? In this lecture, Professor Walter J. Veith looks at the document, “From Conflict to Communion,” with a special focus on statements on salvation, justification, and atonement. What is Mary’s role in bringing all religions together? What role does the charismatic movement play in bringing about world unity? 

Were the issues that sparked the Protestant Reformation resolved by Vatican II or have they intensified? The signing of this document negates every principle that Protestants once stood for and marginalizes our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ. Are Protestants moving complacently toward a precipice? What seems so congenial may just contain the sting of death. 

Discover more: https://amazingdiscoveries.org
